<doc id="32318" wikidata="Q527779" url="?curid=32318" title="Ulysses">
<text>Ulysses is the Latin name for Odysseus, a legendary Greek hero recognized for his intelligence and cunning. He is famous for his long, adventurous journey home to Ithaca after the Trojan War, as narrated in Homer&#x27;s Odyssey.

Ulysses may also refer to:
