==Properties==

===Basic properties===
Variance is non-negative because the squares are positive or zero:
formula_49

The variance of a constant is zero.
formula_50

Conversely, if the variance of a random variable is 0, then it is almost surely a constant. That is, it always has the same value:
formula_51

===Issues of finiteness===
If a distribution does not have a finite expected value, as is the case for the Cauchy distribution, then the variance cannot be finite either. However, some distributions may not have a finite variance, despite their expected value being finite. An example is a Pareto distribution whose index formula_52 satisfies formula_53

